      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "fresh"
    },
    {
      "name": "Olive oil",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "extra virgin"
    },
    {
      "name": "Chopped fresh parsley",
      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "for garnish"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "In a large clay tagine or Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat.",
    "Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly browned, about 8 minutes.",
    "Add garlic, cumin, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.",
    "Add chickpeas, lemon juice, and kabanos sausages; stir to combine.",
    "Bring mixture to a simmer, then reduce heat to low and cook, covered, for 25 minutes.",
    "Stir in chopped parsley; continue cooking, covered, for an additional 5-10 minutes.",
    "Remove from heat and let cool slightly before serving."
  ],
